OL,3,CMan who burnt down MP's office denies
OL,4,Ctargeting politician
OL,6,FThe case was listed on Friday (19
OL,7,FDecember) at Newcastle Crown Court to
OL,8,Ffix a sentencing date.
OL,10,FJolyon Perks, prosecuting, outlined
OL,11,Fthe background to the offences, saying
OL,12,FOliver was discharged from the army
OL,13,Fbecause of his behaviour and went to
OL,14,Flive with his father.
OL,16,FMr Perks said the defendant's father
OL,17,Fconfirmed a "significant
OL,18,Fdeterioration" in his son's mental
OL,19,Fhealth, which led to him living rough
OL,20,Fnear the offices.
